WEBVTT

00:00:00.031 --> 00:00:02.521
A patient lies on a table in a hospital treatment

00:00:02.582 --> 00:00:04.409
room. The door is closed.

00:00:05.172 --> 00:00:07.101
The room is empty except for the patient and the

00:00:07.141 --> 00:00:09.050
machine. In the next room,

00:00:09.070 --> 00:00:10.653
an operator sits at a console.

00:00:11.434 --> 00:00:13.077
She has entered the treatment parameters.

00:00:13.858 --> 00:00:15.320
The screen confirms the settings.

00:00:16.142 --> 00:00:18.085
She presses the key to activate the beam.

00:00:18.946 --> 00:00:21.350
The machine fires. The screen updates:

00:00:22.051 --> 00:00:24.074
treatment complete. Normal dose.

00:00:24.755 --> 00:00:27.500
No error. The patient feels a sudden,

00:00:28.061 --> 00:00:31.526
intense burning like a hot wire pressed against the skin.

00:00:32.588 --> 00:00:35.252
She calls out. The intercom is off.

00:00:35.252 --> 00:00:38.155
She gets up. She finds someone.

00:00:38.876 --> 00:00:40.137
She says something went wrong.

00:00:41.178 --> 00:00:42.699
The operator checks the console.

00:00:43.560 --> 00:00:45.422
The readout shows a routine treatment.

00:00:46.103 --> 00:00:47.264
The dose log is normal.

00:00:47.884 --> 00:00:49.306
The machine recorded no fault.

00:00:50.086 --> 00:00:50.927
One of them is wrong.

00:00:51.748 --> 00:00:53.510
The patient, or the machine.

00:00:54.491 --> 00:00:55.972
The hospital believes the machine.

00:00:56.953 --> 00:00:59.235
This is a story about what happens when a system

00:00:59.315 --> 00:01:02.839
earns trust it was never tested enough to deserve and

00:01:02.879 --> 00:01:05.121
what it costs when that trust finally breaks.

00:01:06.130 --> 00:01:09.896
Radiation therapy works by aiming a beam of high-energy particles

00:01:10.017 --> 00:01:13.042
at a tumor. The goal is to deliver enough energy

00:01:13.102 --> 00:01:17.489
to destroy cancerous cells while leaving the surrounding tissue intact.

00:01:18.330 --> 00:01:19.372
The margin is narrow.

00:01:19.973 --> 00:01:22.297
Too little dose and the treatment fails.

00:01:23.078 --> 00:01:25.723
Too much and you burn healthy tissue,

00:01:26.264 --> 00:01:28.287
damage organs, kill the patient.

00:01:29.269 --> 00:01:32.374
The machine exists to hold that margin.

00:01:32.374 --> 00:01:35.242
A medical linear accelerator can operate in two modes.

00:01:35.944 --> 00:01:40.115
In electron mode, the beam hits the patient directly useful

00:01:40.155 --> 00:01:42.381
for tumors near the surface.

00:01:42.850 --> 00:01:46.134
In X-ray mode, the electron beam strikes a metal target

00:01:46.235 --> 00:01:49.799
first, which converts it into X-rays that can penetrate deeper.

00:01:49.819 --> 00:01:54.366
In X-ray mode, a flattening filter spreads the beam evenly

00:01:54.426 --> 00:01:55.647
across the treatment area.

00:01:56.549 --> 00:01:59.252
The distinction matters. In electron mode,

00:01:59.833 --> 00:02:02.817
the beam is relatively low energy and diffuse.

00:02:02.817 --> 00:02:05.581
In X-ray mode without the target and filter in place,

00:02:06.302 --> 00:02:10.888
the full-power electron beam would hit the patient concentrated and

00:02:10.968 --> 00:02:13.532
unshielded. That is not a treatment.

00:02:14.213 --> 00:02:15.014
That is an injury.

00:02:15.935 --> 00:02:18.358
The machine's job is to make sure the beam mode

00:02:19.059 --> 00:02:21.562
and the physical hardware configuration always match.

00:02:22.364 --> 00:02:24.006
If the operator selects X-ray,

00:02:24.747 --> 00:02:27.070
the target and filter must be in the beam path.

00:02:27.831 --> 00:02:30.795
If they are not, the machine must not fire.

00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:33.811
That rule is the entire safety architecture.

00:02:34.732 --> 00:02:36.594
Everything depends on it being enforced.

00:02:37.495 --> 00:02:39.758
The Therac-25 was not a new machine.

00:02:40.399 --> 00:02:42.561
It was the third in a series built by Atomic

00:02:42.641 --> 00:02:43.883
Energy of Canada Limited.

00:02:44.744 --> 00:02:49.610
Its predecessors the Therac-6 and Therac-20 had been in clinical

00:02:49.730 --> 00:02:53.855
use for years. Those earlier machines had software controlling the

00:02:53.895 --> 00:02:56.778
beam. But they also had something else:

00:02:57.880 --> 00:03:03.438
hardware interlocks. Physical mechanisms in the beam path that prevented

00:03:03.478 --> 00:03:06.049
dangerous configurations from reaching the patient,

00:03:06.792 --> 00:03:09.102
regardless of what the software did.

00:03:09.385 --> 00:03:11.208
If the software set up the wrong mode,

00:03:11.990 --> 00:03:12.871
the hardware caught it.

00:03:13.733 --> 00:03:17.059
A mechanical fuse between intention and consequence.

00:03:18.020 --> 00:03:21.166
The software could fail, and the patient would still be

00:03:21.246 --> 00:03:27.217
safe. The Therac-25 removed the hardware interlocks.

00:03:27.237 --> 00:03:29.140
Software would handle safety directly.

00:03:29.901 --> 00:03:33.047
No physical backup. No mechanical check.

00:03:33.314 --> 00:03:37.078
The reasoning was straightforward: the software had been used in

00:03:37.118 --> 00:03:39.241
the earlier models. It had worked.

00:03:40.021 --> 00:03:41.403
It had never caused an accident.

00:03:42.404 --> 00:03:46.048
Why duplicate safety with expensive hardware when the code was

00:03:46.128 --> 00:03:48.911
already proven? That reasoning had a flaw.

00:03:49.592 --> 00:03:52.295
The software in the earlier machines had never been tested

00:03:52.335 --> 00:03:55.959
operating alone. It had always run behind the hardware safety

00:03:55.999 --> 00:03:59.283
net. The fact that no software failure had caused an

00:03:59.403 --> 00:04:02.967
accident did not mean the software could not fail.

00:04:02.967 --> 00:04:05.089
It meant the hardware had never needed to catch a

00:04:05.170 --> 00:04:09.955
failure visibly. The absence of a visible problem was treated

00:04:10.055 --> 00:04:12.938
as proof that no problem existed.

00:04:12.978 --> 00:04:16.442
The safety net was removed because it had never been

00:04:16.522 --> 00:04:19.586
seen catching anything. And the machine shipped.

00:04:20.287 --> 00:04:24.351
The Therac-25's software had a flaw that only appeared under

00:04:24.411 --> 00:04:28.944
specific conditions. The operator interface let you type in treatment

00:04:28.984 --> 00:04:30.987
parameters, then edit them.

00:04:31.968 --> 00:04:32.969
If you typed a command,

00:04:32.969 --> 00:04:35.573
moved the cursor up to change a field,

00:04:36.253 --> 00:04:39.017
and re-entered the correct value within a narrow time window

00:04:39.798 --> 00:04:43.423
roughly eight seconds the software could enter a state where

00:04:43.463 --> 00:04:46.787
the beam mode displayed on screen no longer matched the

00:04:46.847 --> 00:04:51.201
physical hardware configuration. The screen would show X-ray mode.

00:04:51.982 --> 00:04:54.625
The machine would be configured for direct electron beam.

00:04:55.406 --> 00:04:56.487
No target in the path.

00:04:57.067 --> 00:05:01.392
No flattening filter. Full-power electrons aimed straight at the patient.

00:05:02.213 --> 00:05:03.454
This was a race condition.

00:05:04.215 --> 00:05:08.320
A timing-dependent bug. The software used a shared variable that

00:05:08.360 --> 00:05:11.603
could be overwritten if the operator edited faster than the

00:05:11.663 --> 00:05:16.246
machine could reconfigure. The counter that tracked the setup process

00:05:16.306 --> 00:05:18.691
would overflow, skip the safety check,

00:05:19.292 --> 00:05:21.035
and leave the hardware in the wrong state.

00:05:22.118 --> 00:05:23.520
In the earlier Therac models,

00:05:24.122 --> 00:05:25.404
this would not have mattered.

00:05:26.246 --> 00:05:29.232
The hardware interlock would have physically blocked the beam.

00:05:29.633 --> 00:05:33.921
In the Therac-25, there was nothing between the bug and

00:05:33.941 --> 00:05:36.686
the patient. The overdose was massive.

00:05:37.668 --> 00:05:41.535
Patients received doses estimated at 100 times the intended amount,

00:05:42.216 --> 00:05:45.482
concentrated into a beam a few millimeters wide.

00:05:45.563 --> 00:05:46.785
In a fraction of a second.

00:05:47.667 --> 00:05:48.990
And the console would display:

00:05:49.030 --> 00:05:52.356
treatment complete. No error.

00:05:53.358 --> 00:05:58.869
Sometimes a cryptic message appeared MALFUNCTION 54 with no explanation

00:05:58.909 --> 00:06:01.515
of what it meant, no indication of severity,

00:06:02.136 --> 00:06:04.821
and a prompt that allowed the operator to simply press

00:06:04.962 --> 00:06:08.917
P to proceed. Operators learned to press P.

00:06:09.919 --> 00:06:12.142
The message came up often enough to feel routine.

00:06:13.084 --> 00:06:14.126
It was background noise.

00:06:14.867 --> 00:06:17.812
Here is how a machine earns trust it does not

00:06:17.872 --> 00:06:20.236
deserve. Not through deception.

00:06:21.178 --> 00:06:27.028
Through repetition. Layer one: inherited reputation.

00:06:27.028 --> 00:06:30.533
The Therac-25's software was carried forward from earlier models.

00:06:31.374 --> 00:06:33.798
Code that has been running in the field feels tested.

00:06:33.818 --> 00:06:35.641
It carries a track record.

00:06:36.462 --> 00:06:40.127
But the track record belonged to a different context one

00:06:40.167 --> 00:06:44.313
where hardware interlocks caught any software failure before it reached

00:06:44.353 --> 00:06:46.937
the patient. The reputation was real.

00:06:47.678 --> 00:06:50.923
The safety it implied was not.

00:06:50.923 --> 00:06:53.926
Layer two: removed safeguards.

00:06:54.908 --> 00:06:56.549
The hardware interlocks were taken out.

00:06:57.450 --> 00:06:59.212
This was framed as simplification.

00:07:00.013 --> 00:07:02.476
An improvement. Fewer moving parts.

00:07:03.137 --> 00:07:07.202
Lower cost. No one performed a systematic analysis of what

00:07:07.222 --> 00:07:09.124
the software would need to handle on its own,

00:07:09.724 --> 00:07:11.867
because no one believed the software would fail in a

00:07:11.927 --> 00:07:15.411
way that mattered. Layer three:

00:07:15.411 --> 00:07:19.000
successful operation. The machine shipped to hospitals.

00:07:19.561 --> 00:07:21.684
It ran treatments. Hundreds of them.

00:07:22.204 --> 00:07:26.230
Thousands. Treatments completed. Patients received their doses.

00:07:26.951 --> 00:07:31.316
No alarms. Each successful session reinforced the same conclusion:

00:07:31.977 --> 00:07:35.362
the machine works. Layer four:

00:07:35.362 --> 00:07:38.966
normalized error messages. When errors did appear,

00:07:39.006 --> 00:07:42.589
they were cryptic. MALFUNCTION 54.

00:07:42.929 --> 00:07:46.472
No explanation. No severity level.

00:07:47.193 --> 00:07:49.635
No instruction to stop treatment and investigate.

00:07:50.556 --> 00:07:52.758
Operators saw these messages regularly.

00:07:52.778 --> 00:07:56.521
They learned that pressing P and retrying usually worked.

00:07:57.322 --> 00:07:59.563
The interface trained them to override warnings,

00:08:00.124 --> 00:08:02.606
because the warnings had never meant anything before.

00:08:03.927 --> 00:08:07.350
Layer five: the instrument over the patient.

00:08:08.140 --> 00:08:10.785
When patients reported pain burning,

00:08:11.245 --> 00:08:15.613
stinging, sensations that did not match a normal treatment the

00:08:15.653 --> 00:08:18.498
machine's dose log showed a normal delivery.

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:21.523
The data said everything was fine.

00:08:22.245 --> 00:08:23.487
The patient said it was not.

00:08:24.328 --> 00:08:26.312
And in a system built on the assumption that the

00:08:26.352 --> 00:08:29.237
machine was reliable, the data won.

00:08:29.740 --> 00:08:33.847
This chain inherited trust, removed safeguards,

00:08:34.528 --> 00:08:37.854
reinforced by repetition, normalized errors,

00:08:38.615 --> 00:08:43.604
instrument over patient is the same structural pattern as Challenger's

00:08:43.604 --> 00:08:47.530
warning-softening chain, running in a completely different domain.

00:08:48.432 --> 00:08:51.036
In both cases, the system was not lying.

00:08:51.898 --> 00:08:53.841
It was not hiding anything.

00:08:53.841 --> 00:08:57.305
It was simply operating on a definition of safety that

00:08:57.365 --> 00:09:01.109
had never been stress-tested against the conditions that would break

00:09:01.189 --> 00:09:03.611
it. The conditions arrived.

00:09:04.652 --> 00:09:08.016
Between June 1985 and January 1987,

00:09:08.136 --> 00:09:13.502
the Therac-25 was involved in at least six known radiation

00:09:13.562 --> 00:09:17.105
overdose incidents at hospitals in the United States and Canada.

00:09:18.086 --> 00:09:20.689
Three patients died from their injuries.

00:09:20.804 --> 00:09:23.133
Others suffered severe radiation burns,

00:09:23.936 --> 00:09:27.490
neurological damage, and long-term disability.

00:09:28.111 --> 00:09:31.254
The first reported accident was at a clinic in Georgia

00:09:31.274 --> 00:09:36.039
in 1985. A patient received a massive overdose.

00:09:36.059 --> 00:09:39.642
She developed radiation burns consistent with far more energy than

00:09:39.682 --> 00:09:43.245
the prescribed treatment. The hospital reported the incident to the

00:09:43.285 --> 00:09:49.171
manufacturer, AECL. AECL investigated.

00:09:50.072 --> 00:09:51.453
They could not reproduce the error.

00:09:52.374 --> 00:09:56.298
Their conclusion: the machine's safety systems made such an overdose

00:09:56.378 --> 00:09:59.883
impossible. The problem must have been elsewhere.

00:09:59.923 --> 00:10:03.689
A second incident occurred at a different hospital.

00:10:04.711 --> 00:10:07.575
Same symptoms. Same machine behavior.

00:10:08.397 --> 00:10:10.921
Treatment complete. No error.

00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:15.769
AECL again could not reproduce the fault.

00:10:16.053 --> 00:10:18.776
Again concluded the machine was not responsible.

00:10:19.717 --> 00:10:22.239
Then came the incident that cracked the case open.

00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:24.702
An operator in Tyler, Texas,

00:10:25.202 --> 00:10:29.727
had noticed something. When she entered parameters in a specific

00:10:29.807 --> 00:10:34.632
sequence typing one mode, then quickly correcting to another the

00:10:34.672 --> 00:10:39.657
machine displayed MALFUNCTION 54 and delivered only a partial dose.

00:10:40.698 --> 00:10:42.880
She would press P, retry,

00:10:43.381 --> 00:10:44.862
and the same thing happened.

00:10:45.483 --> 00:10:47.625
On one occasion she retried three times.

00:10:48.326 --> 00:10:50.148
The patient, lying on the table,

00:10:50.729 --> 00:10:53.311
received three massive overdoses in succession.

00:10:54.092 --> 00:10:55.213
He died five months later.

00:10:55.253 --> 00:10:59.098
The operator reported the exact keystroke sequence.

00:11:00.079 --> 00:11:01.420
She had identified the trigger.

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:04.603
AECL issued a software patch.

00:11:05.304 --> 00:11:07.927
The patch addressed that specific input sequence.

00:11:08.728 --> 00:11:12.392
More accidents followed. The patch had fixed one path to

00:11:12.432 --> 00:11:16.377
the bug, but the underlying architecture the race condition,

00:11:16.898 --> 00:11:21.026
the shared variable, the missing hardware check was still there.

00:11:22.048 --> 00:11:24.834
Other keystroke sequences could trigger the same failure.

00:11:25.816 --> 00:11:28.721
Each incident was handled as a one-off.

00:11:28.741 --> 00:11:31.567
Each investigation started from the assumption that the machine was

00:11:31.667 --> 00:11:36.096
fundamentally sound. And no mechanism existed to connect reports across

00:11:36.136 --> 00:11:39.490
hospitals. A physicist at one clinic had no way of

00:11:39.550 --> 00:11:41.393
knowing that a physicist at another clinic,

00:11:41.974 --> 00:11:45.059
a thousand miles away, was seeing the same thing.

00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:46.962
The pattern was there.

00:11:47.944 --> 00:11:49.547
No one was looking at the whole picture.

00:11:50.468 --> 00:11:53.112
The investigation that finally exposed the full scope of the

00:11:53.173 --> 00:11:56.959
problem was driven largely by a hospital physicist named Fritz

00:11:57.019 --> 00:12:00.124
Hager at the East Texas Cancer Center.

00:12:00.357 --> 00:12:05.102
After the Tyler incidents, Hager refused to accept AECL's assurance

00:12:05.522 --> 00:12:06.523
that the machine was safe.

00:12:07.524 --> 00:12:08.726
He conducted his own tests.

00:12:09.707 --> 00:12:12.189
He replicated the operator's keystroke sequence.

00:12:13.110 --> 00:12:14.111
He measured the output.

00:12:15.012 --> 00:12:18.636
He found that the machine could deliver radiation doses orders

00:12:18.716 --> 00:12:21.319
of magnitude above what the console displayed.

00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:23.581
He contacted the FDA.

00:12:24.222 --> 00:12:25.683
He contacted other hospitals.

00:12:26.464 --> 00:12:30.128
He started connecting incidents that had been treated as unrelated.

00:12:30.128 --> 00:12:33.313
What Hager demonstrated was not just a technical defect.

00:12:33.994 --> 00:12:35.497
It was a structural failure:

00:12:36.378 --> 00:12:39.904
the manufacturer's investigation process could not find the problem

00:12:40.445 --> 00:12:43.370
because it started from the assumption that the machine was

00:12:43.410 --> 00:12:47.136
reliable. Every test was designed to confirm safety,

00:12:47.677 --> 00:12:49.720
not to probe for failure.

00:12:49.720 --> 00:12:52.442
The question was never "under what conditions could this machine

00:12:52.502 --> 00:12:57.026
hurt someone?" The question was "can we reproduce the specific

00:12:57.046 --> 00:12:59.548
reported error?" And when they could not,

00:13:00.089 --> 00:13:01.070
the case was closed.

00:13:01.950 --> 00:13:04.372
The same inversion of proof that appeared in the Challenger

00:13:04.453 --> 00:13:07.735
decision meeting. The burden was on the failure to prove

00:13:07.795 --> 00:13:10.778
itself, not on the system to prove its safety.

00:13:11.639 --> 00:13:13.020
Once the full picture emerged,

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:14.921
the failures were not subtle.

00:13:15.862 --> 00:13:19.065
The software had no independent safety monitoring.

00:13:19.518 --> 00:13:22.645
The same code that controlled the beam also decided whether

00:13:22.665 --> 00:13:24.288
the beam was safe.

00:13:24.308 --> 00:13:26.954
There was no separate system watching for dangerous states.

00:13:27.655 --> 00:13:30.321
The error messages shown to operators were meaningless.

00:13:31.022 --> 00:13:32.766
Numeric codes with no description,

00:13:33.568 --> 00:13:37.155
no severity ranking, no instruction to stop.

00:13:37.155 --> 00:13:39.938
The interface was not designed to communicate danger.

00:13:40.698 --> 00:13:43.221
It was designed to communicate workflow status.

00:13:43.962 --> 00:13:48.066
There was no hardware dose monitor that could independently detect

00:13:48.126 --> 00:13:49.467
an overdose in real time.

00:13:50.248 --> 00:13:53.151
The machine trusted its own software to report its own

00:13:53.271 --> 00:13:56.394
errors. That is like asking someone to grade their own

00:13:56.434 --> 00:14:00.818
exam. The manufacturer had not performed a systematic failure-mode

00:14:00.818 --> 00:14:02.940
analysis on the software.

00:14:02.940 --> 00:14:06.145
No one had asked: what happens if the setup routine

00:14:06.225 --> 00:14:09.971
is interrupted? What happens if the operator edits faster than

00:14:10.011 --> 00:14:13.757
the machine reconfigures? What happens if the counter overflows?

00:14:14.879 --> 00:14:18.385
And the FDA's regulatory framework was not equipped to evaluate

00:14:18.385 --> 00:14:22.792
software-dependent medical devices. The agency had authority over the

00:14:22.832 --> 00:14:25.576
hardware. The software lived in a gap.

00:14:26.558 --> 00:14:31.664
Two causes. A software defect that allowed a lethal mismatch

00:14:31.744 --> 00:14:34.688
between beam mode and hardware configuration.

00:14:35.890 --> 00:14:38.935
And an organizational system manufacturer,

00:14:39.395 --> 00:14:44.483
regulator, hospital that was structured to confirm the machine worked

00:14:45.043 --> 00:14:46.946
rather than to discover how it could fail.

00:14:47.787 --> 00:14:50.872
The Therac-25 did not fail despite the system.

00:14:51.733 --> 00:14:55.118
It failed because the system was designed to trust itself.

00:14:55.118 --> 00:14:58.162
The Therac-25 is now one of the most cited case

00:14:58.202 --> 00:15:01.786
studies in software engineering, medical device regulation,

00:15:01.846 --> 00:15:03.828
and safety system design.

00:15:03.888 --> 00:15:06.511
Not because it was the worst accident.

00:15:07.252 --> 00:15:10.016
Because the pattern it revealed keeps showing up.

00:15:10.016 --> 00:15:14.721
Carried-forward code inherits a reputation it may not have earned

00:15:14.801 --> 00:15:15.762
in the new context.

00:15:16.783 --> 00:15:20.167
Removing a safety layer is treated as simplification,

00:15:20.888 --> 00:15:24.092
not as a change that requires its own risk analysis.

00:15:24.427 --> 00:15:27.871
Operators adapt to unreliable signals by learning to ignore them

00:15:28.711 --> 00:15:32.636
which means real warnings get the same response as false

00:15:32.696 --> 00:15:35.999
alarms. And when a machine says one thing and a

00:15:36.079 --> 00:15:39.683
person says another, the default is to believe the machine.

00:15:40.784 --> 00:15:43.267
The case did produce real change.

00:15:44.208 --> 00:15:48.272
The FDA expanded its authority to cover software in medical

00:15:48.332 --> 00:15:53.405
devices. The principle of defense in depth never rely on

00:15:53.445 --> 00:15:57.050
a single layer for safety was reinforced as a binding

00:15:57.110 --> 00:15:59.194
design standard for radiation equipment.

00:16:00.115 --> 00:16:02.919
Independent hardware dose monitors became expected,

00:16:03.520 --> 00:16:08.127
not optional. And incident-reporting mechanisms across hospitals were

00:16:08.187 --> 00:16:12.233
strengthened so that patterns invisible to individual sites could be

00:16:12.273 --> 00:16:16.199
caught. But the deeper question the one that makes this

00:16:16.359 --> 00:16:19.733
more than a historical case is how we build trust

00:16:19.813 --> 00:16:22.958
in systems that are too complex to fully test.

00:16:24.060 --> 00:16:27.245
Autonomous vehicles run millions of miles without incident,

00:16:27.886 --> 00:16:30.491
and each mile builds confidence.

00:16:30.511 --> 00:16:33.435
But the confidence is in the conditions that have been

00:16:33.475 --> 00:16:37.482
driven, not in the conditions that have not.

00:16:38.052 --> 00:16:42.457
Algorithmic decision systems in healthcare and criminal justice compile

00:16:42.557 --> 00:16:46.542
track records of outputs, and those track records become the

00:16:46.642 --> 00:16:51.148
evidence of reliability. But the track record only covers what

00:16:51.188 --> 00:16:54.232
has been measured. The question is always the same.

00:16:55.033 --> 00:16:57.976
Has the system been tested under the conditions where it

00:16:58.036 --> 00:17:00.960
could fail? Or only under the conditions where it has

00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:06.272
succeeded? The Therac-25 answered that question with six patients who

00:17:06.312 --> 00:17:07.775
did not know they were the test.

00:17:08.676 --> 00:17:11.061
The most dangerous kind of trust is the kind that

00:17:11.101 --> 00:17:12.203
has never been tested.

00:17:12.263 --> 00:17:17.493
Only repeated. The Therac-25 did not fail because the people

00:17:17.573 --> 00:17:18.695
around it were careless.

00:17:19.577 --> 00:17:23.263
It failed because every layer of the system the engineers

00:17:23.324 --> 00:17:25.187
who carried the code forward,

00:17:25.187 --> 00:17:27.330
the manufacturer who removed the interlocks,

00:17:27.950 --> 00:17:30.113
the operators who learned to override the errors,

00:17:30.814 --> 00:17:34.037
the regulators who had not caught up to software had

00:17:34.097 --> 00:17:35.939
built confidence on the same foundation:

00:17:36.700 --> 00:17:38.062
the machine had worked before.

00:17:38.102 --> 00:17:41.726
That was true. It was also incomplete.

00:17:41.726 --> 00:17:45.991
And incomplete, in a system where the consequences are measured

00:17:46.051 --> 00:17:49.335
in human tissue, is not the same as safe.

00:17:49.822 --> 00:17:50.887
The failure was real.

00:17:51.671 --> 00:17:52.998
The cause chain was longer.

00:17:53.862 --> 00:17:56.395
Next time: another design failure.

00:17:57.159 --> 00:18:00.597
Another system that taught itself to ignore what it already

00:18:00.657 --> 00:18:01.300
knew.
